==Old English==
===Etymology===
Representing a reduplicative form of an original Indo-European base ''*gno-'' (Greek [[γιγνώσκειν]], Latin [[noscere]] etc.).  There are Germanic cognates in Old High German ''-cnāhen'', Old Norse [[kná]]; from the same PIE source are [[kennan]], [[cannan]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈknaːwan/}}

